annotation.TEXT: This room's the same as always.
Ha! I stealthily grab the fifth Yoshi coin! I'm pretty sure I was supposed to just kill the Urchin with the Goomba to reach that normally though.
Oh, right. I want to collect these coins in a particular way so that I can check something.
Huh. Its name isn't in atbash. Maybe the "all atbash" thing was just for that previous level? (Oh, but the "Well on the way" level had its name translated...)
So, I guess I'm heading to the Yellow Switch now (which I probably could've easily fit into the previous episode, but whatever).
Oh, this is new-- A fake light blue pipe.
Ah, but the note blocks did go all the way to the right, so I wasn't supposed to reach that flower? Perhaps, seeing how there's another flower right here.
That setup's still the same as before... But, wait. Wasn't there a Yoshi coin just beyond that wall?
Hey, did you just see that? He jumped completely over my stomp attempt!
That would've been silly if I had bounced that flower up before revealing the invisible note blocks, and then had it get stuck up there!
Gah! What I dain say just bramaged about did getting not?
Ooh, this pipe actually goes somewhere now.
It's actually the same name as before: "Well on the way".
Silly non-solid corner tile. Also, gold cement blocks?
40 from the ground. I'll take it. And, that gives me enough stars for a bonus game!
Heck yeah. Runnin' on-- Wait a minute. I see duders down there!
Oh, but this message has been translated. Okay, translating it back, it says: "-HDRGXS KZOZXV- You have found the lost yellow blocks! They will be returned to their proper places."

Aww... Why'd you move it way down here? Sure, its original position allowed for an exploit with cloned turn blocks, but it also required a Yoshi that I can't get until later. I think you should've left the Yoshi coin right where it was.
Wow, I could get tons of coins from these multi-coin blocks. However, I'm really low on time. I'm hoping (and expecting) that this pipe will just drop me off right next to the goal.
Nuts. Not quite. Perhaps if I had brought a goomba over here to be included in the combo...
Demo count: 1
And there's the goal. Same as before.
Huh. More fake gold blocks. Whatever.
Oh, heck, yeah! It had been a while since I'd gotten a 50!
Huh. I see the goal sphere that was wedged in between the pipes here has been removed.
The position of this block has definitely changed, because I now have to duck to hit it. Hey, is Mr. Banzai Bill still over here?
Seems about the same as before. Hey, maybe I should actually put some effort into collecting the coins up there this time.
Nailed it! Sweet!
D'oh! Mario, are you still dain bramaged?
Alright, foodge that evil bonus room and its evil exit (that I was expecting to have me come out of this green pipe), and let's head straight to the goal!
This tower of Babel or whatever is still the same, but there's now a Lava Lotus to the right that wasn't there before.
Money, money, money!
Is there enough for a 1-up combo here?
Gotcha that time! (Thanks, Bullet Bill!)
The main feature of this setup is still the same, but I like how you've replaced the cement blocks with nicer-looking grassy terrain.
So, there are now steps for me to climb up to it normally, but what's up there?
Not nearly enough for a 1-up combo though. Also, I can tell this yellow pipe is totally fake.
What the? I can walk on water now? What madness is this?!
The Pokey is still the same, but the green pipe on the right extends off the bottom of the screen now, not that it affects normal gameplay.
Huh. The posts and purple coin column here seem to have shrunk quite a bit. I wonder why you changed that...
Aw... It was removed instead of becoming the entrance to a cool bonus room like I had suggested before? Man...
And of course, hitting the block normally to get a blue P-switch is how you get past this brown wall.
Thanks again, Bullet Bills! (Huh, the bottom bullet vanished there for some reason.)
Whoa, it's Chuck city over here! Did I stumble onto their training grounds or something?
Hey there, Baseball Chuck in the ground. How's it going?
Oh, but there appears to be more stuff added to this part now!
Huh. The key is now in the third ? block instead of the fourth.
...And not kick the shell the wrong way... Let me try that again...
Okay, let's see if I can 1-up combo these koopas this time. I think I should be able to if I stomp enough of them first.
Well, either the invisible note block row didn't go all the way to the right, or I just reached something I shouldn't have! But, it's just a flower. Nothing game-breaking.
There's the goal, but of course, I've gotta check every pipe! (Also, I'm missing a Yoshi coin for some reason.)
D'oh, I burnt the shell. Fireballs really interfere with block cloning if you're using a flammable or inflammable thing to do it. Also, this pipe still goes nowhere.
Ohhh... Crap. I wasted the P-switch before, so how do I get across this pit?
So, what's new here?
Hey there duders, and welcome back to some insane island somewhere.
Maybe I can 1-up combo these guys?
A multi-coin block. Ooh, I so want to block factory this!
Last time, on Greenman's Island of Insanity V3, I ended the video by getting this secret exit.
Go my yellow blocks, and fill the world with your bvooldmvhh!
That MOOOONNN is still up in the corner, right?
Oh, and I see the vine and the spinning turn block and cannon column has been removed in favor of a simple triple-decker cannon.
Moon count: 1
At least I got my 1-up!
By the way, I'm pretty good at video games, in case you couldn't tell.
Awesome. You've kept this tricky Yoshi coin setup, and you removed the unnecessary cannon objects that weren't actually firing bullets. Nice.
Yep, and I saw that that tall ledge is still there.
Yes! Awesome! Also, the munchers up here are now supported by cement blocks, so they won't be left floating when a P-switch is hit.
And, bonus points for that 50 being trickier to achieve than usual!
Alright, now that that's taken care of, let's head on over to the next level.
A key, and a goal fish in the wall? Also, an Urchin and a Goomba, which will fall to my mighty silver P-switch! ...Oh, that's right. It acts like a blue P-switch now.
Ah, they're fake. Of course. I should've known.
Alright, next time, I go "Grtsg ilkv dzoprmt". What does that mean? Find out next time (or just translate it yourself)! To be continued...
This coin trail still isn't perfect. It's not exactly easy to collect them all in one jump. Compare with your first such coin trail in this level, which is much better made.
Nope. Not quite. I was just one hit short.
Don't let the atbash fool you. This level's name is still "Tiger's walk".

Well, that sucks. Now I have to repeat the second half of the level! (I thought about rewinding out of that cheap death, but the fifth Yoshi coin required me to go through that bonus room, so I'll just keep going from here.)
What the?! Umm... Greenman? I think this secondary exit is broken! You might want to fix that!
Cool! I'm glad the key isn't flammable or inflammable!
Hey, can I maybe block clone myself a silver P-switch or two?
Ooh. I know the cannons have been adjusted, but I want to see if I can pull off a 1-up combo here anyway... And try not to get dain bramaged in the process...
Okay, now is there still a P-switch door near midpoint here?
By pretending this is Kaizo Mario World! That's how!
Oh, and once again, the moon and demo counts have been reset for this new version of the hack.
The cement blocks up here have been replaced with grassy terrain once again. It totally looks nicer, even if it still functions about the same.
What the? Let me reach that ? block! ...Wait. Maybe if I carefully sneak in from the right...

I bet it's because the wall between the pipes over here is thicker now, causing the stuff to the right to be shifted by one space, but the key block had to remain in its particular X position. Otherwise, it would've become something else.
